  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "DA+SSoUeowb+O5O5IYdR607JqgI=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:33.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# ecosystem map\n\nThe complete Powerhouse document model ecosystem as reported by switchboard CLI. 21 domain models, 346 total operations, organized into 5 functional zones.\n\n## Service & Pricing (6 models, 155 ops)\n\nThe core of this project. These models define the product catalog, commercialization, and subscription lifecycle.\n\n- [[facet model provides configurable classification dimensions]] \u2014 6 ops, categorical options consumed by templates and offerings\n- [[resource-template model defines reusable service catalog blueprints]] \u2014 28 ops, product-level configuration without pricing\n- [[service-offering model defines tiered pricing with option groups and service groups]] \u2014 51 ops (largest), tiered pricing and configuration\n- [[service-subscription model tracks service-level subscription agreements]] \u2014 12 ops, agreement-level subscription tracking\n- [[subscription-instance model tracks active customer subscriptions with lifecycle state]] \u2014 39 ops, individual customer subscription with billing\n- [[resource-instance model tracks provisioned resource lifecycle]] \u2014 19 ops, provisioned resources with lifecycle state machine\n\nData flow: Facet \u2192 ResourceTemplate \u2192 ServiceOffering \u2192 ServiceSubscription \u2192 SubscriptionInstance \u2192 ResourceInstance\n\n## Finance & Billing (4 models, 37 ops)\n\nFinancial recording and billing infrastructure.\n\n- [[accounts model defines the chart of accounts structure]] \u2014 4 ops, foundation account entities\n- [[account-transactions model tracks financial transaction records]] \u2014 10 ops, debit/credit recording\n- [[billing-statement model captures periodic billing summaries]] \u2014 7 ops, periodic billing aggregation\n- [[payment-terms model defines payment conditions and schedules]] \u2014 16 ops, payment conditions and terms\n\n## Reporting (3 models, 67 ops)\n\nOutput documents \u2014 invoices, expense claims, snapshots.\n\n- [[invoice model generates formal payment requests]] \u2014 31 ops (second largest), formal invoice generation\n- [[expense-report model tracks expense claims and approvals]] \u2014 18 ops, expense claim workflow\n- [[snapshot-report model provides point-in-time data captures]] \u2014 18 ops, point-in-time archival\n\n## Organization & Identity (4 models, 29 ops)\n\nWho operates in the ecosystem \u2014 builders, teams, networks.\n\n- [[builder-profile model describes individual contributor identities]] \u2014 12 ops, individual contributor profiles (referenced by SO.operatorId)\n- [[builders model aggregates builder collections]] \u2014 2 ops (smallest), builder directory\n- [[network-profile model represents network-level organizational entities]] \u2014 11 ops, DAOs and ecosystem networks\n- [[operational-hub-profile model defines operational hub configurations]] \u2014 4 ops, teams and working groups\n\n## Work Management (3 models, 48 ops)\n\nProject scoping, procurement, and work organization.\n\n- [[scope-of-work model structures deliverables and milestones]] \u2014 33 ops (third largest), project deliverables and budgets\n- [[request-for-proposals model manages procurement workflows]] \u2014 6 ops, procurement funnel\n- [[workstream model organizes ongoing work streams]] \u2014 9 ops, portfolio-level grouping\n\n## Cross-Zone Dependencies\n\n- ServiceOffering.`operatorId` \u2192 BuilderProfile (Service & Pricing \u2192 Organization)\n- SubscriptionInstance \u2192 BillingStatement (Service & Pricing \u2192 Finance)\n- SubscriptionInstance \u2192 Invoice (Service & Pricing \u2192 Reporting)\n- ScopeOfWork \u2192 Invoice (Work Management \u2192 Reporting, milestone billing)\n- ScopeOfWork \u2192 BuilderProfile (Work Management \u2192 Organization, assignees)\n\n## Token Economics / Revenue Distribution (1 model, requirements stage)\n\nRevenue distribution and token holder economics. New zone introduced by the POWA system.\n\n- [[powa-revenue-distribution model captures epoch-based token revenue sharing]] \u2014 requirements stage, epoch-based multi-token revenue distribution with governance lifecycle\n\nData flow: EpochConfig \u2192 RevenueDeposit \u2192 DistributionRecord \u2192 ClaimEvent\n\n## Local Project Scope\n\nThis repository implements 5 of the 21 models (Facet, ResourceTemplate, ServiceOffering, SubscriptionInstance, ResourceInstance) with 4 editors. The POWA revenue distribution model is in requirements stage (not yet implemented). The remaining 16 models exist in the broader Powerhouse ecosystem.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[index]]",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:33.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:33.000Z"
    }
  },
